{
  "stem": "26765.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But my aunt, I think, was one of these unfortunate people who had really swallowed, been brainwashed by all of the propaganda that had been taught in Germany, and in other countries too, for generations so that she herself, I think, was not comfortable with her Jewish background.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that's very sad.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She was very depressed for many, many years.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I don't think that she was ever able to sort it out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did, but I really did not know how to tell them when they were little about Bergen-Belsen, that I did not know how to broach that subject.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I wrote a little story for them when they were a little, and I focused on the experiences in Holland mainly.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if I did talk about the concentration camp or the experience, I spoke about the liberation in Trobitz.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was only later on when they were adults when my daughter studied history in college that she said to me, Ma, everybody knew in Germany what was happening with the Jews because the entire country was mobilized-- not that the people could do anything because once Hitler came to power, there was nothing you can do unless you wanted to get shot, but everybody knew, she said to me.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, in 1985, that was the 40th anniversary of the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, before then, I am in the field of I'm a psychiatric nurse.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you know you have to have a certain amount of therapy yourself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I saw my aunt so depressed, I was fearful that maybe as time went by that I would really lapse into a depression.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I did seek some help, and I had a wonderful psychiatrist who did help me.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
